column1: # Definition: The indicator considers people's evaluation of their life as a whole. It is a weighted-sum of different response categories based on people's rates of their current life relative to the best and worst possible lives for them on a scale from 0 to 10, using the Cantril Ladder (known also as the "Self-Anchoring Striving Scale").
# Data from the No Ceilings project: http://noceilings.org
# For more about the data, please visit http://noceilings.org/data
